<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=549&amp;p=4665#p4665"><![CDATA[
Even if we emulate an NES whose PPU generates component signals instead of emulating down to the level of NTSC composite or S-video signals, a lot of commercial and homebrew games such as <em>Super C</em> take advantage of the fact that the top and bottom are cut off so that they can hide the garbage when an attribute block is split across the top and bottom of the screen.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Sun Sep 18, 2005 1:40 pm</p><hr />
