<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=549&amp;p=4512#p4512</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=549&amp;p=4512#p4512"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Nintendulator/sprite issues...]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=549&amp;p=4512#p4512"><![CDATA[
Disable sprites via $2001 when the level is not loaded, and/or clear the whole OAM with any value from $f0 to $ff, so all sprites won't be visible.<br />Not doing sprite DMA in a frame won't make sprites to disapear, they'll just stand where they were the last frame without moving.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Tue Sep 13, 2005 8:49 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
