Never mind, I fixed it. Okay, I was wondering something. What if you want things in your NMI to happen, but you want some things in your routine to happen at different times? Like, I want to increment vbl_count constantly, but I don't always want my sprite sitting there on the screen. How could I avoid this? Okay, this is bad, but I was thinking of something like this:<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">nmi:<br />       inc vbl_count<br />       lda rmlod    ;variable for saying room is loaded<br />       cmp #1      ; if variable is 1 &#40;I add one to this variable when the room is loaded&#41;<br />       beq continue<br />       rti<br /><br />continue:<br />       lda #0<br />       sta $2003<br />       jsr handlepad       ; joypad<br />       lda #high&#40;cynthi&#41;<br />       sta $4014<br />       rts<br /></div><br /><br />it's because I only want my sprite to appear when the level is loaded. I tried that, didn't work, because I'm bad at coding. Okay, any suggestions?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=138">Celius</a> — Mon Sep 12, 2005 8:39 pm</p><hr />
